channel.title: Error with compile.bat and runserver.bat
channel.description:
My Compile.bat seems to be working fine now :D
My runserver.bat says this, not sure what this should be aiming at, or what to do:
[code]@echo off title CheezScape Server java -Xmx512m -cp .;./jython.jar;./MySql/mysql-connector-java-3.0.17-ga-bin.jar server[/code]
When I run my runserver.bat, it replies:
[code]Error: Unable to startup listener on 43594 - port already in use? config\objects.cfg: file not found[/code]
I can't find the objects.cfg, so the runserver.bat isn't lying :| Sounds stupid but, where do I get an objects.cfg file? And why is the port 43594 already in use? How?
Any help please?

item.title: Error with compile.bat and runserver.bat
item.dc:creator: @xsaberjrx xsaberjrx
item.description:
@xsaberjrx wrote:

What you do is this. Open up your start menu Click on Run. Type in tskill java and then re open your runserver. This makes sure that you have any hidden/minimized runservers open that you cannot close.
